@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Lifting Weights";
}

<div class="container text-center mt-4">
    <h1>Welcome to My Website About Lifting!</h1>

    <div class="row mt-4">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="/images/lifting1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded" alt="Incline Bench Press" style="width: 50%;">
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <img src="/images/lifting2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded" alt="Hanging Leg Raise" style="width: 50%;">
        </div>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-4">
        Lifting weights is one of the healthiest hobbies you can have! Here are some of the benefits:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
        <li class="list-group-item">Stronger muscles</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Increased bone density</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Better cardiovascular health</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Better mental health</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Weightlifting, particularly hypertrophy training, is an excellent way to build strength, improve overall health,
        and increase muscle mass. Hypertrophy training focuses on maximizing muscle growth through moderate to heavy weights
        with higher repetitions. This type of training stimulates muscle fibers, leading to muscle enlargement, improved 
        endurance, and greater strength over time. It also boosts metabolism, supports joint health, and enhances body composition
        Beyond just the physical benefits, weightlifting is a great way to reduce stress, improve mental health, and increase 
        confidence as you see your progress.</p> 
        <br />
        <p>
        To maximize the benefits of weightlifting, it's important to follow a balanced workout split that targets different 
        muscle groups effectively. A typical training split might involve training each muscle group multiple times a week. 
        For example, a common split is the Push-Pull-Legs routine, where you focus on pushing muscles (chest, shoulders, triceps)
        one day, pulling muscles (back, biceps) another day, and legs on a separate day. This structure ensures that you're hitting
        all the major muscle groups while giving them time to recover between workouts. By combining proper training with adequate 
        nutrition and rest, you can achieve significant gains and improve your overall fitness.
    </p>
    <a href="@Url.Action("Calculator", "Home")" class="btn btn-primary mt-3">Go to Tutoring Calculator</a>
</div>
